	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				As to the post about pets using weapons.  Pets get a great deal here.<BR>
A pet has it's dam/delay ratio of dam/30 normally *Damage depends on level*<BR>
A level 4 pet (summoned at lvl 4, not 5 or 3) can hit for 10 damage.  so 10/30 isn't bad.  This is where it gets a tad tricky.<BR>
Given a fine steel dagger (3/19) the pet will inherit only the better stat...since weapons' damage is only half of what the pet can actually do with it...this should be 6 damage, 19 delay for a pet...however, like I said, the pet only takes the attributes that are better than it's own already...so the pet (remember, base of 10/30) becomes 10/19...quite an improvement...<BR>
By the same token, given a rusty halberd (10/56), he will again recieve only the stat better than his already and become 20/30 (20 because he hits for twice the shown damage on the weapon, as in all melee)!  Not a bad pet at all.<BR>
I hope this helps all starting necros...by level 16 or so, there aren't many cheap weapons (if any) that will give the pet damage better than it's base...so try to get fine steel daggers for a pet...take it's delay from 30 to 19! :)<BR>
<BR>
&gt;&gt;&gt;Redthorne Mistwalker - 25th season Druid&lt;&lt;&lt;<BR>
<BR>
P.S. I do have a level 13 necro, so I do know what I'm talking about :)
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
