			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				There seems to be a lot of confusion here so let me tell you what I know about pets.  I am an Iksar Necro lvl 11.  This spell takes 2 bone chips (not 3).  And my pet is definitely better with a weapon.  He takes its delay/damage attributes.  Also, the pet does seem to take exp away from each kill.  It seems to me the more damage he does as compared to you has alot to do with the amount of experience you get from each kill.  So don't just let the pet tank while you sit back.  You should tank a little and/or cast so that you do damage also.  
